Robin Cura | Geography and GIScience

Current position

Associate Professor of GIScience and Geography at Panthéon-Sorbonne University, member of the PRODIG research lab.

Bio

Robin Cura is an Associate Professor of Geography at Panthéon-Sorbonne University. His work focuses on quantitative geography, agent-based modelling and data visualization. With a background in geographic data science and geographic information engineering, he is interested in the development of quantitative methods for the exploration, vizualization and analysis of spatial data.

Education

Université Paris 1 Panthéon-Sorbonne | Paris, France

  • Ph.D. in Geography within the Géographie-cités research lab | 2013 - 2020
    Thesis (in french) : “Interdisciplinary modelling of settlement systems through the collective : co-construction and visual analysis of a simulation model”

  • Master Carthagéo : Geography, GIScience and Cartography | 2008 - 2011
